A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 40-1-1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 definitions relative to motor vehicles and traffic, so as to revise the definition of
3 "multipurpose off-highway vehicle"; to amend Article 10 of Chapter 5 of Title 48 of the
4 Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to ad valorem taxation of motor vehicles and
5 motor homes, so as to define "multipurpose off-highway vehicle" and subclassify such
6 vehicles for ad valorem taxation purposes; to provide that such vehicles shall not be returned
7 or taxed for ad valorem taxation purposes; to provide for related matters; to provide for an
8 effective date and applicability; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
10 SECTION 1.
11 Code Section 40-1-1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to definitions
12 relative to motor vehicles and traffic, is amended by revising paragraph (33.1) as follows:
13 "(33.1)(A) 'Multipurpose off-highway vehicle' means any self-propelled, motorized
14 vehicle having features that:
15 (i) Has features specifically intended for utility use; and having the following
16 characteristics:
17 (ii) Was originally manufactured to be primarily used off-highway;
