18 (A)(iii) Has the capability to transport persons or cargo or both;
19 (B)(iv) Operates between 25 miles per hour (40.2 40 kilometers per hour) and 65
20 miles per hour (104.6 105 kilometers per hour);
21 (C)(v) Has an overall width of 80 inches (2,030 millimeters) (203 centimeters) or
22 less, exclusive of accessories or attachments;
23 (D)(vi) Is designed to travel on four or more wheels;
24 (E)(vii) Uses a steering wheel for steering control;
25 (F)(viii) Contains a nonstraddle seat;
26 (G)(ix) Has a gross vehicle weight rating of less than 4,000 pounds (1,814
27 kilograms); and
28 (H)(x) Has a minimum cargo capacity of 350 pounds (159 kilograms).
29 (B) Such term shall not include any all-terrain vehicle, low-speed vehicle, passenger
30 car, or personal transportation vehicle."
31 SECTION 2.
32 Article 10 of Chapter 5 of Title 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to ad
33 valorem taxation of motor vehicles and motor homes, is amended by adding a new part to
34 read as follows:
35 "Part 8
36 48-5-504.50.
37 (a) As used in this Code section, the term 'multipurpose off-highway vehicle' shall have
38 the same meaning as set forth in Code Section 40-1-1.
39 (b) As authorized pursuant to Article VII, Section I, Paragraph III(b)(3) of the Constitution
40 of Georgia, multipurpose off-highway vehicles shall constitute a separate classification of
41 self-propelled vehicles for ad valorem taxation purposes.
